(Finding #4: [High] Redeemer-tainted arithmetic in options.spend) Tj T*
(  Detector: unsafe-redeemer-arithmetic) Tj T*
(  Module: options) Tj T*
(  Location: validators/options.ak:696) Tj T*
(Description: Handler options.spend uses division with redeemer-derived variables) Tj T*
(    \(tainted: [redeemer]\). The redeemer is attacker-controlled — using it directly in) Tj T*
(    arithmetic risks division-by-zero, overflow, or precision manipulation.) Tj T*
(Recommendation: Validate redeemer values before arithmetic: `expect redeemer.value > 0` or) Tj T*
(    use datum-sourced values instead.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Finding #5: [High] Multi-asset comparison bypass possible in options.spend) Tj T*
(  Detector: multi-asset-comparison-bypass) Tj T*
(  Module: options) Tj T*
(  Location: validators/options.ak:696) Tj T*
(Description: Handler options.spend uses assets.match with inequality comparator. An) Tj T*
(    attacker can inject extra assets not covered by the comparison.) Tj T*
(  Recommendation: Use == comparator in assets.match for exact Value matching.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Finding #6: [High] Multi-asset comparison bypass possible in options.mint) Tj T*
(  Detector: multi-asset-comparison-bypass) Tj T*
(  Module: options) Tj T*
(  Location: validators/options.ak:760) Tj T*
(Description: Handler options.mint uses assets.match with inequality comparator. An) Tj T*
(    attacker can inject extra assets not covered by the comparison.) Tj T*
(  Recommendation: Use == comparator in assets.match for exact Value matching.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Finding #7: [Medium] Datum field 'issuer_bech32_address' in options.spend has unbounded) Tj T*
(  type) Tj T*
(  Detector: unbounded-datum-size) Tj T*
(  Module: types) Tj T*
(  Location: lib/types.ak:51) Tj T*
(Description: Field 'issuer_bech32_address' has type 'ByteArray' which can grow) Tj T*
(    unboundedly. Processing a large datum may exceed Plutus execution budget.) Tj T*
(Recommendation: Consider using bounded alternatives or enforcing size limits in validator) Tj T*
(    logic.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Finding #8: [Medium] Inequality match comparator on Value in options.spend may miss assets) Tj T*
(  Detector: value-comparison-semantics) Tj T*
(  Module: options) Tj T*
(  Location: validators/options.ak:696) Tj T*
(Description: Handler options.spend uses `assets.match` with an inequality comparator \(>=,) Tj T*
(    >\) alongside value arithmetic. This only checks that listed assets meet minimums —) Tj T*
(    extra unexpected assets in the output are silently accepted.) Tj T*
(Recommendation: Use `==` comparator in `assets.match` for exact Value matching, or) Tj T*
(    explicitly check that no unexpected assets are present.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
